                                                   !!! IMPORTANT CONSIDERATIONS !!!

- Always read the information displayed by the shell on login
- Avoid installing software and dependendcies that are known to be targets of supply chain attacks (Ex. NodeJS)
- Do not write to the .bashrc file without testing changes locally
- Remember to always update the github upon any changes made to .bashrc, motd or network configurations
- Remember to actually disconnect from Termux once you are done
- Stick to using the prefered RDP client (Remmina) unless absolutely necessary
- SCP won't work with current .bashrc configuration. Comment it out before trying it
- If you must reload rhe shell, run the command source .bashrc to do so. Avoid logging in and out all the time
- Avoid creating useless files in the home or user directory

